Most extreme value theorem-based MPPT papers do not consider this kind of PV operating conditions, which may result in a wrong perturbation, causing incorrect tracking trajectory, especially when there is a rapid change in solar irradiance. For conventional extreme value theorem-based MPPT controller, two points on the tracking trajectory are required to calculate the ratio of ΔP/ΔV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
