For all cases, three parameters, i.e., duty cycle, power of PV panel and voltage of PV panel, are monitored. Towards to all cases, the performances of the conventional P&O MPPT technique and the proposed MPPC technique are individually explained as follows.
Starting stage: for the proposed MPPC technique, only two perturbations are adequate to track the MPP, whereas the conventional P&O technique requires several perturbations. For P&O, loss exists for the solar energy, and voltage fluctuation continues for a long time, and their magnitudes are dependent on the perturbation period and ΔD\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
